article.headline: Brown 64, Quinnipiac 60
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- Freshman forward Scott Friske scored a career-high 26 points, including four free throws in the final 25 seconds, to lead Brown to a 64-60 non-conference win over Quinnipiac at Burt Kahn Court. Brown closed the game with an 8-4 run after Quinnipiac tied the game at 56-56 with 5:28 left on two free throws from sophomore center Karl Anderson. Quinnipiac would score just one point over the next 5:14, until Craig Benson hit a 3-pointer from the left corner with 14 seconds remaining to pull the Bobcats within 61-60. Brown sophomore guard Damon Huffman, an 83 percent free throw shooter, made one of two free throws with 13 seconds left. Sophomore center Damon McDonald was able to tip a loose ball rebound in the lane out to Marcus Becker, who swung the ball to Friske. Friske was fouled and made both of his free throws with 6 seconds left. Friske also had 10 rebounds. Becker, Huffman and Keenan Jeppesen all had seven points for Brown. Brown, which led by as many as 12 in the second half, improved to 4-9. Quinnipiac lost its fourth straight to drop to 5-7. Junior guard Adam Gonzalez and senior guard Craig Benson each had 16 to lead Quinnipiac. Senior forward Kevin Jolley added 12 points and 11 rebounds.
